parts.text:
```json
{
  "application": "Dflow-FM",
  "software": [
    "Singularity",
    "Intel compiler 2021a",
    "SLURM workload manager"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 32,
    "memory": "40G",
    "time": "03:30:00",
    "partition": "thin"
  },
  "input_files": [
    "gtsm_fine_hmdg.mdu",
    "run_dflowfm.sh"
  ],
  "output_files": [
    "newsingularity.done"
  ],
  "commands": [
    "module purge",
    "module load 2021",
    "module load intel/2021a",
    "$singularityFolder/execute_singularity_snellius.sh $modelFolder run_dflowfm.sh --partition:ndomains=$SLURM_NTASKS:icgsolver=6 $mduFile",
    "$singularityFolder/execute_singularity_snellius.sh $modelFolder run_dflowfm.sh -m $mduFile"
  ],
  "description": "This script runs a Dflow-FM model using Singularity on the Snellius supercomputer. It utilizes a specified MDU file (gtsm_fine_hmdg.mdu) and runs the model using the provided execute_singularity_snellius.sh script. The script takes advantage of SLURM for resource allocation and job management."
}
```
